text: Elo rating Gamil Agamaliev (), Turkish spelling Cemil Aghamaliyev, (born 31 August 1974) is an Azerbaijani chess Grandmaster, now resident of Turkey. He played for Azerbaijan in the World Youth U26 Team Chess Championship of 1993. In 2005, he finished fifth in the 2nd Kish GM tournament in Iran. In 2014 he transferred to Turkey, where he now spells his name as Cemil Aghamaliyev.FIDE transfers, 2014 His handle on the Internet Chess Club is "Sheki". ==References== ==External links== * * Category:1974 births Category:Living people Category:Chess grandmasters Category:Azerbaijani chess players
